ts Act of 1965 (52 U.S.C. Sec. 10101 et seq.), that informs voters of all of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 5.5em;">(I) An all-mailed ballot election is being conducted and each eligible voter will be issued a vote by mail ballot by mail.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 5.5em;">(II) The voter may cast a vote by mail ballot in person at a vote center during the times and days specified in subparagraph (A) of paragraph (4) or on election day.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 5.5em;">(III) No later than seven days before the day of the election, the voter may request
